{"lemma": "زِيادَةٌ", "slug": "زِيادَةٌ", "root": "ز.#.د", "root_slug": "ز-_-د", "root_link": "/words/roots/ز-_-د", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "زِيادَة", "root": "زيد", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 2}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 2}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n18493"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "increase", "fa": "افزایش", "ur": "اضافہ", "tr": "artış", "id": "peningkatan", "bn": "বৃদ্ধি", "es": "aumento", "fr": "augmentation", "de": "Erhöhung", "ru": "увеличение", "zh": "增加"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of زَادَ (zāda) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb", "uncountable"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "increase, surplus, addition"}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/zi.jaː.da/", "/zjaː.da/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n18493", "headword_ar": "زِيَادَةٌ", "root": "zyd", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "an inf. n. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAda", "text_ar": "زَادَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, Msb.) Using it as an inf. n., (Msb,) you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AifoEalo *`lika ziyaAdapF", "text_ar": "اِفْعَلْ ذٰلِكَ زِيَادَةً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Do thou that in addition"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S, Msb:) the vulgar say ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAy^idapF", "text_ar": "زَايِدَةً", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) which one should not say. (Msb.) [Hence also,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Huruwfu Alz~iyaAdapi", "text_ar": "حُرُوفُ الزِّيَادَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The letters of augmentation;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the augmentative letters;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the letters that are added to the radical letters in Arabic words"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]:"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "they are ten, and are"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1276}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "comprised in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saA^alotumuwniyhaA", "text_ar": "سَاَلْتُمُونِيهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[“ Ye asked me for them ”], (TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aloyawoma tanosaAhu", "text_ar": "اَلْيَوْمَ تَنْسَاهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[“ Today thou wilt forget it ”]; (K, TA;) and more than a hundred and thirty other combinations comprising them have been mentioned: (MF:) [these letters are also called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zawaAy^idu", "text_ar": "زَوَايِدُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", of which the sing. is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAy^idapN", "text_ar": "زَايِدَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zayodN", "text_ar": "زَيْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b2-  [As a simple subst., or a subst. properly so termed, it signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "An increase,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "increment; and augmentation,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "augment; an addition, additament, adjunct,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "accessory: an accession: excess, redundance,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "superfluity:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a redundant part"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "portion"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "appertenance; a surplus; a residue: an excrescence:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ziyaAdaAtN", "text_ar": "زِيَادَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zayAy^idu", "text_ar": "زَيايِدُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b3-  Hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ibilN", "text_ar": "اـِبِلٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaviyrapu Alz~ayaAy^idi", "text_ar": "كَثِيرَةُ الزَّيَايِدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i.e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alz~iyaAdaAt", "text_ar": "الزِّيَادَات"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Camels having much increase;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "lit.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "much,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "many, increases"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (K.) A poet says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "bihajomapK tamolaA^u Eayona AlHaAsidi\n                      \n                     \n                        *aAti suruwHK jam~api Alz~ayaAy^idi"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "With a herd of forty or more camels, that fill,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "glut, the eye of the envier, enjoying pasturing by themselves, having much increase"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: some say, [in citing this verse,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alz~awaAy^idi", "text_ar": "الزَّوَايِدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is pl. of ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAy^idapN", "text_ar": "زَايِدَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlzwAy^d", "text_ar": "الزوايد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is said only in relation to the legs of a beast. (L.) ―         -b4-  [Hence also,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ziyaAdapu Alkabidi", "text_ar": "زِيَادَةُ الكَبِدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (so in a copy of the S, and in the A and L, and in several places in the K,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alkabidi", "text_ar": "الكَبِدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAy^idapu", "text_ar": "زَايِدَةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (so termed by Zj, and so in the T, and in two copies of the S, and in the L,) both of which are correct, (TA,) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The redundant appertenance of the liver;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a certain small piece to which the liver is attached,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "suspended:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Zj, in his “ Khalk el-Insán: ”) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a certain small appertenance of the liver"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "hunay~apN minohaA SagiyrapN", "text_ar": "هُنَيَّةٌ مِنْهَا صَغِيرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "),"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "at its side, going away from it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mutanaH~iyapN EanohaA", "text_ar": "مُتَنَحِّيَةٌ عَنْهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "): (S, L:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a certain piece appended,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "attached, to the liver"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muEal~aqapN bihaA", "text_ar": "مُعَلَّقَةٌ بِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "): (A:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a certain appendage of the liver;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[so I render"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "hanapN", "text_ar": "هَنَةٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mutaEal~iqapN minohaA", "text_ar": "مُتَعَلِّقَةٌ مِنْهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", agreeably with the next preceding explanation; though it may be rendered"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a thing suspended from it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i.e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from the liver;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or the right reading may be"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "hnp mtEl~qp bihaA", "text_ar": "هنة متعلّقة بِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is virtually the same as the explanation in the A, and agreeable with what here follows: so called] because"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it is a redundance"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "taziydu", "text_ar": "تَزِيدُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upon its upper surface:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L:) [all of these explanations seem to denote"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the round ligament of the liver:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the Hebrew"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "יֹחֶרֶח הַכּבֵד", "text_ar": "יֹחֶרֶח הַכּבֵד", "orth_type": "plain"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in Ex. xxix. 22, literally signifies the same; like the slightly-varying appellations in Ex. xxix. 13 and Lev. iii. 4, and Lev. ix. 10: but the real meaning thereof is much disputed: the rendering of the LXX. is"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "λοβὸσ τοῦ  ἥπατοσ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; which is said to mean"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "extrema pars hepatis:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "that of the Vulg.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "reticulum hepatis:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "that of our authorized Engl. Vers.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the caul above the liver;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(with this marginal note: “ it seemeth by anatomy, and the Hebrew Doctors, to be"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the midriff: ”"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") and it is remarkable that this is one of the meanings assigned to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alxilobu", "text_ar": "الخِلْبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which some hold to be syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zayaAdapu Alkabidi", "text_ar": "زَيَادَةُ الكَبِدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilobN", "text_ar": "خِلْبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) Bochart (in his Hieroz. t. i., p. 498, seq.,) and Gesenius (in his Lex.) explain the Hebrew term as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the greater lobe of the liver:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "but this is hard to reconcile with the Hebrew or the Arabic; and utterly irreconcileable with the explanations given by the Arabs; among whom, it should be observed, were many of the Jewish religion, who cannot reasonably be supposed to have not known the correct meaning of a term relating to their sacrifices:] the pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zyAdp", "text_ar": "زيادة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zayaAy^idu", "text_ar": "زَيَايِدُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (L,) and that of ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zAy^dp", "text_ar": "زايدة", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zawaAy^idu", "text_ar": "زَوَايِدُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, L.) Hence the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alwaladu kabidu *iY Alwaladi wawaladu Alwaladi", "text_ar": "الوَلَدُ كَبِدُ ذِى الوَلَدِ وَوَلَدُ الوَلَدِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ziyaAdapu Alkabidi", "text_ar": "زِيَادَةُ الكَبِدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The child is as the liver of the parent, and the grandchild is"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the redundant appertenance of the liver"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A, TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["Msb", "S", "TA", "MF", "L", "A"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}